net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component

Class ComponentDisplay

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ComponentDisplay
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, HTMLClassifier
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ButtonDisplay, FieldDisplay, ListDisplay, MediaDisplay, PagingDisplay, TabDisplay, TableDisplay, TextAreaDisplay

    public class ComponentDisplay
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable, HTMLClassifier
    Defines display properties for a component. This class is used instead of Component members so that display properties can be easily set from other sources.
    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

      • appendDisplayClass

        public void appendDisplayClass(@Nullable
                               java.lang.String string)
        Description copied from interface: HTMLClassifier
        Append a value to the display class. If no display class is set the argument becomes the display class. Otherwise a space is appended to the existing display class and then the argument.

        You can use this method to set multiple classes at once. This method does not check to see if the class names already exist in the display class string.

        Specified by:
        appendDisplayClass in interface HTMLClassifier
        Parameters:
        string - the string to append.
